Table of Measures: Biobehavioral factors (tobacco and alcohol use, physical activity)
Use of psychosocial counseling and support services
Depressive symptoms (Center for Epidemiologic Studies - Depression [CES-D])
IOC v.2 scales (worry, life interference, altruism/empathy)
Cancer-related distress (Impact of Events Scale [IES] - intrusions subscale)
Positive affect (Positive and Negative Affect Scale [PANAS]- positive affect subscale + items for joviality and serenity subscales)
Social support (2-way Social Support Questionnaire - emotional support subscales; Social Provisions Scale - attachment subscale)
Rumination (subscale of Rumination and Reflection Questionnaire [RRQ])
